> Or if you are willing to load every single system font and check if it supports all required characters

For the reference, loading all system fonts and checking script support take less than a second, but results are quite unreliable, since it will include stuff like symbol and emoji fonts. So as character checks are definitely needed (still takes only a few seconds to get a full list).

Sample code:
```c++
String sample = U"一人大中的上出生不年自子地日本同下三小前所是我有了在国到会你他要以時也就可之得十事好那能学家多二和後用天者而心行新看文如道去都想方只手成問然当作主學这資長會来五這個个社市说们月为四為九交來政系業分时";
//from https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/User:Hippietrail/Frequency:Most_Useful_CJK_Characters
Vector<String> fonts = OS::get_singleton()->get_system_fonts();
for (const String &E : fonts) {
	String path = OS::get_singleton()->get_system_font_path(E);
	if (!path.is_empty()) {
		Ref<FontFile> f;
		f.instantiate();
		if (f->load_dynamic_font(path) == OK) {
			if (f->is_script_supported("Hani")) {
				bool ok = true;
				for (int j = 0; j < sample.size(); j++) {
					bool has_char = f->has_char(sample[j]);
					ok = ok && has_char;
					if (!has_char) {
						break;
					}
				}
				if (ok) {
					print_line(vformat("Font: %s %s", E, path));
				}
			}
		}
	}
}
```

